'''阿胡拉山'''（Ahuna Mons）<ref name=IAU>{{Cite web |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15409 |title=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature – Ahuna Mons |accessdate=2015-10-16 |archive-date=2016-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228104213/https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15409 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，早期媒體間多稱為穀神星上的'''金字塔形山峰'''（Pyramid）<ref>For example [http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/video/details.php?id=1392], [http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/spaceimages/details.php?id=PIA19574], [http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2015/06/23/416828532/nasa-flummoxed-by-dwarf-planet-s-bright-spots-pyramid-shaped-peak], [http://www.universetoday.com/122052/ceres-pyramid-gets-a-closer-look-but-bright-spots-remain-a-mystery/]</ref>，是突出在[[矮行星|矮行星]][[穀神星|穀神星]]平滑地表上的一座大山，位於穀神星南半球的[[鏈坑|鏈坑]]群[[烏荷拉鏈坑|烏荷拉鏈坑]]（Uhola Catenae）東方約85公里。學界目前對於阿胡拉山的認知並不多，咸信此山應該不是因為撞擊事件而形成的，並且它很可能是穀神星上唯一一座屬於這種類型的山。明亮的條紋在山坡上從山頂到山腳下；這些條紋被認為是鹽類，類似於鈰矽鈹釔礦的亮點<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://gizmodo.com/ceres-mysterious-bright-spots-arent-made-of-ice-after-a-1734112941 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2015-10-16 |archive-date=2015-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017033730/http://gizmodo.com/ceres-mysterious-bright-spots-arent-made-of-ice-after-a-1734112941 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。它的名稱來自[[印度東北部|印度東北部]][[蘇米娜迦|蘇米娜迦]]（Sumi Naga）部落傳統的收穫節慶典{{link-en|阿胡拉|Sumi Naga#Ahuna}}（Ahuna）。

這座山是從2015年[[曙光號|曙光號]]在環繞穀神星拍攝照片中發現的<ref>{{cite web|title=NASA spies 3-mile-tall 'pyramid,' more bright spots on Ceres|url=http://www.cnet.com/uk/news/3-mile-tall-pyramid-more-bright-spots-spied-on-ceres/|date=17 June 2015|work=Cnet|accessdate=19 June 2015|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303180310/http://www.cnet.com/uk/news/3-mile-tall-pyramid-more-bright-spots-spied-on-ceres/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。估計它的平均高度約4公里（2.5英里或13,000英尺），最陡峭約5公里（3.1英里或16,000英尺）<ref name="NASA-20150806">{{cite web |author= |title=Tall Mountain: Enhanced View
|url=http://dawn.jpl.nasa.gov/multimedia/images/image-detail.html?id=PIA19618 |date=6 August 2015 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |accessdate=6 August 2015 }}</ref>，基部寬約20km（12英里或是66,000英尺）<ref>{{cite web |title='Great Pyramid' spotted on Ceres by NASA's Dawn spacecraft |url=http://www.theweathernetwork.com/news/articles/whats-up-in-space-great-pyramid-of-ceres-mars-conjunction-lunar-dust-cloud/52920/|date=18 June 2015|work=The Weather Network|accessdate=19 June 2015}}</ref>。
